A four-months-pregnant woman, her fiance and her toddler were all killed when their car skidded on an icy road and plowed into a pickup truck.

Sherissa Goodman, 35, lost control of her Chevrolet Lumina on County Road J20 in southern Iowa about 5pm Wednesday, and drove into the path of a vehicle coming the other way.

Goodman and her passengers, 31-year-old Charles Downard and three-year-old Shayla Matte, died at the scene.

The pickup truck driver, 21-year-old Jeremiah Boswell, was rushed to Decatur County Hospital with undisclosed injuries, KCCI reported.

